##Preparing the data
salsa_analytical <- salsa_analytical %>% 
    modify_if(is.labelled, to_factor)


##Creating helper functions
{
survival_estimates <- function(data,
                               id,
                               treated,
                               untreated){
  
  survx1 <- data %>%
    select(!!sym(id), time, !!sym(treated), !!sym(untreated)) %>% 
    group_by(!!sym(id)) %>% 
    mutate(surv0=cumprod(!!sym(untreated)),
           surv1=cumprod(!!sym(treated))) %>% 
    group_by(time) %>% 
    summarise(s0 = mean(surv0),
              s1 = mean(surv1),
              p0 = 1 - s0,
              p1 = 1 - s1,
              RD = p1 - p0,
              RR = p1/p0, .groups = "drop") 
  
  results <- tibble(
    
    estimate  = str_sub(treated, start=14),
    
    RR_ave = exp(mean(log(survx1$p1) - log(survx1$p0))), #average RR over the entire follow-up time
    RD_ave = mean(survx1$p1 - survx1$p0)) #average RD over the entire follow-up time
  
  time_data <- tibble(
    estimate  = str_sub(treated, start=14),
    survx1
  )
  
  return(list(results=results,
              time_data=time_data))
  
}

#a function to convert time
from_time_to_time <- function(old_time_scale="years",
                              new_time_scale="days",
                              time_var = "time"){
  
  if (old_time_scale=="years" & new_time_scale=="days"){
    newtime = time_var*360
  } else if (old_time_scale=="years" & new_time_scale=="months"){
    newtime = time_var*12
  } else if (old_time_scale=="years" & new_time_scale=="years"){
    newtime = time_var
  } else if (old_time_scale=="months" & new_time_scale=="days"){
    newtime = time_var*30
  } else if (old_time_scale=="months" & new_time_scale=="months"){
    newtime = time_var
  } else if (old_time_scale=="months" & new_time_scale=="years"){
    newtime = time_var/12
  } else if (old_time_scale=="days" & new_time_scale=="days"){
    newtime = time_var
  } else if (old_time_scale=="days" & new_time_scale=="months"){
    newtime = time_var/30
  } else if (old_time_scale=="days" & new_time_scale=="years"){
    newtime = time_var/360
  } else {
    stop("verify the unites: must yearS, monthS or dayS")
  }
  
  return(round(newtime,0))
}

gform_te_survival <- function(data,
                              time_var = "time_to_dementia_cind_yrs",
                              old_time_scale= "years",
                              new_time_scale= "months",
                              exposure = list(name="high_accult", dist="binary"),
                              outcome  = list(name="dementia_cind",  dist="binary",
                                              covariates=confounder_vars),
                              plot_data =FALSE) {
  
  
  dsn1 <- data %>% 
    mutate(event_date_mos = from_time_to_time(old_time_scale = old_time_scale, 
                                              new_time_scale = new_time_scale, 
                                              time_var = !!sym(time_var))) # converting time
  
  #Get a bootstrap sample from the data
  bootdata <- sample_n(dsn1, size = nrow(dsn1), replace = TRUE)
  bootdata %<>%  
    mutate(id=1:nrow(.))
  n <- nrow(bootdata)
  
  var_names <- bootdata %>% select(-c({{time_var}})) %>% colnames()
  
  bootdata_long <- bootdata %>% 
    tidyr::expand(nesting(!!!syms(var_names)), time=as.double(0:(max(event_date_mos)-1))) %>% 
    mutate(censored = case_when((time>=event_date_mos & !!sym(outcome$name)==0)~1, 
                                TRUE~0),
           current_event = case_when((time>=event_date_mos-1 & !!sym(outcome$name)==1)~1, 
                                     TRUE~0)) %>% 
    group_by(id) %>% 
    mutate(past_event = lag(current_event),
           past_event = case_when(is.na(past_event)~0,
                                  TRUE~past_event))
  
  bootdata_long_restricted <- bootdata_long %>%
    filter(past_event==0 & censored==0)
  
  formula_y = formula(ifelse(length(outcome$covariates) == 0, 
                             glue("current_event ~ {exposure$name}*poly(time, 2, raw = T)"),
                             glue("current_event ~ {exposure$name}*poly(time, 2, raw = T) + ", glue_collapse(outcome$covariates, sep=" + "))))
  
  
  #Get regression coefficients
  model_y <- glm(formula_y, data=bootdata_long_restricted, family=binomial("logit"))
  
  
  # predicting the prop remaining at risk up to tk
  
  #TE
  bootdata_long$survk1 <- 1 - predict.glm(model_y,
                                          newdata = bootdata_long %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=1), 
                                          type = "response")
  
  bootdata_long$survk0 <- 1 - predict.glm(model_y,
                                          newdata = bootdata_long %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=0), 
                                          type = "response")
  
  te <- survival_estimates(data=bootdata_long, id="id", treated="survk1",untreated="survk0")
  
  
  te$results$estimate <- "TE"
  te$time_data$estimate <- "TE"
  
  if(length(outcome$covariates) == 0){
    outcov = "None"
  } else {
    outcov = glue_collapse(outcome$covariates, sep=" + ")
  }
  
  final_res <- 
    tibble(
      variables = glue("exposure = ", exposure$name, 
                       ", outcome = ", outcome$name,
                       "outcov = ", outcov),
      te$results
    )
  
  
  
  final_res_time_data <- 
    tibble(
      variables = glue("exposure = ", exposure$name, 
                       ", outcome = ", outcome$name,
                       "outcov = ", outcov),
      te$time_data
    )
  

  
  if (plot_data==FALSE){
    return(final_res) 
    
  } else {
    return(final_res_time_data)
  }
  
}  
  
gform_te_survival_all <- function(list_interv0=list_interv, plot){ #Total effect with the plot
  res <- pmap_dfr(list_interv0, 
                  gform_te_survival, 
                  data=salsa_analytical,
                  time_var = "time_to_dementia_cind_yrs",
                  old_time_scale= "years",
                  new_time_scale= "months",
                  plot_data =plot) 
  return(res)
}
}

  

#creating a list
exposure1 <- list(name="high_accult",       dist="binary")
outcome1  <-  list(name="dementia_cind",  dist="binary", 
                   covariates=NULL)
outcome2  <-  list(name="dementia_cind",  dist="binary", 
                   covariates=confounder_vars)
exposure <- c(list(exposure1))
outcome <-  c(list(outcome1, outcome2))

list_interv  <- expand_grid(exposure, outcome) 



#Bootstrap for SE and confidence interval
set.seed(123)
bootsize=200
results_bootsamples_surv_te <- map_dfr(1:bootsize, ~ gform_te_survival_all(list_interv0=list_interv,
                                                                       plot=F),
                                       .id = "replication",
                                       .progress=T) 

    

# Getting the summary statistics of the bootstrap

results_final_surv_te <- results_bootsamples_surv_te %>% 
  mutate_at(vars(contains(c("RR"))), log) %>% 
  set_colnames(str_replace_all(colnames(.), c("RR"="log_RR"))) %>% 
  select(-c(replication)) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols= -c("variables", "estimate"),
               names_to = "effect_type",
               values_to = "value") %>% 
  group_by(variables, effect_type, estimate) %>% 
  group_modify(~ {.x %>% map_dfr(simulr::pestimate_tblx, 
                                 functions=c("N", 'Mean', "Sd", "p2.5th", "p97.5th"))}) %>% 
  select(-c(Variables)) %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% 
  mutate(Mean = case_when(str_detect(effect_type, "log")~exp(Mean), TRUE~Mean),
         `p2.5th` = case_when(str_detect(effect_type, "log")~exp(`p2.5th`), TRUE~`p2.5th`),
         `p97.5th` = case_when(str_detect(effect_type, "log")~exp(`p97.5th`), TRUE~`p97.5th`),
         effect_type= str_replace_all(effect_type, "log_", "")) 


results_adj_crude <- results_final_surv_te %>% 
  mutate(adjusted = case_when(str_detect(variables, "income_5cat")~"adjusted",
         TRUE~"crude")) %>% #to select adjusted model
  filter(str_detect(effect_type, "RR_ave")) %>% 
  select(-c(estimate, N,Sd, variables)) 



knitr::kable(results_adj_crude %>% simulr::round_df(2) , 
             caption = "Total effect of acculturation on incident dementia/CIND") %>%
  kableExtra::kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "bordered"),
                full_width = F)

## Creating some functions
gform_mediation_survival <- function(data=salsa_analytical,
                                               time_var = "time_to_dementia_cind_yrs",
                                               old_time_scale= "years",
                                               new_time_scale= "months",
                                               exposure = list(name="high_accult", dist="binary"),
                                               mediator = list(name="",dist="binary",
                                                               covariates=confounder_vars),
                                               outcome  = list(name="dementia_cind",
                                                               dist="binary",
                                                               covariates=confounder_vars)){
 
  
  dsn1 <- data %>% 
    mutate(event_date_mos = from_time_to_time(old_time_scale = old_time_scale, 
                                              new_time_scale = new_time_scale, 
                                              time_var = !!sym(time_var))) # converting time in months. Could also convert in weeks
  
  #Get a bootstrap sample from the data
  bootdata <- sample_n(dsn1, size = nrow(dsn1), replace = TRUE)
  bootdata %<>%  
    mutate(id=1:nrow(.))
  n <- nrow(bootdata)
  
  var_names <- bootdata %>% select(-c({{time_var}})) %>% colnames()
  
  bootdata_long <- bootdata %>% 
    tidyr::expand(nesting(!!!syms(var_names)), time=as.double(0:(max(event_date_mos)-1))) %>% 
    mutate(censored = case_when((time>=event_date_mos & !!sym(outcome$name)==0)~1, 
                                TRUE~0),
           current_event = case_when((time>=event_date_mos-1 & !!sym(outcome$name)==1)~1, 
                                     TRUE~0)) %>% 
    group_by(id) %>% 
    mutate(past_event = lag(current_event),
           past_event = case_when(is.na(past_event)~0,
                                  TRUE~past_event)) %>% 
    ungroup()
  
  
  bootdata_long_restricted <- bootdata_long %>% 
    filter(past_event==0 & censored==0)
  
  
  #Get marginal means and standard deviations
  mu_x <- mean(as.matrix(bootdata[,exposure$name]), na.rm = T)
  sd_x <- sd(as.matrix(bootdata[,exposure$name]), na.rm = T)
  
  mu_m <- mean(as.matrix(bootdata[,mediator$name]), na.rm = T)
  sd_m <- sd(as.matrix(bootdata[,mediator$name]), na.rm = T)
  
  
  formula_m = formula(ifelse(length(mediator$covariates) == 0, 
                             glue("{mediator$name} ~ {exposure$name}"),
                             glue("{mediator$name} ~ {exposure$name} + ", glue_collapse(mediator$covariates, sep=" + "))))
  
  formula_y = formula(ifelse(length(outcome$covariates) == 0, 
                             glue("current_event ~ {exposure$name}*{mediator$name}*poly(time, 2, raw = T)"),
                             glue("current_event ~ {exposure$name}*{mediator$name}*poly(time, 2, raw = T) + ", glue_collapse(outcome$covariates, sep=" + "))))
  
  
  
  #Get regression coefficients
  model_y <- glm(formula_y, data=bootdata_long_restricted, family=quasibinomial("logit"))
  
  if (mediator$dist == "binary") {
    
    
    
    model_m <- glm(formula_m, data=bootdata, family=quasibinomial("logit"))
    
  } else if (mediator$dist == "continuous") {
    
    model_m <- glm(formula_m, data=bootdata, family=gaussian("identity"))
    
    
  } else {
    stop("mediator$dist must be either binary or continuous")
  }
  #1) no need to simulate covariates
  
  #2) Simulate interventions
  # X stage
  dox_ref  = 0
  dox_idx  = 1
  
  
  #M stage: M_dox
  
  mu_m_dox_ref <- predict(model_m,
                          newdata = bootdata %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=dox_ref), 
                          type = "response")
  
  mu_m_dox_idx <- predict(model_m,
                          newdata = bootdata %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=dox_idx), 
                          type = "response")
  
  
  dom_ref  = 0
  dom_idx  = 1
  
  
  if (mediator$dist == "binary") {
    
    bootdata$m_dox_ref  <- rbinom(n, size = 1, prob = mu_m_dox_ref)
    bootdata$m_dox_idx  <- rbinom(n, size = 1, prob = mu_m_dox_idx)
    
    bootdata$dom_int    <- rbinom(n, size = 1, prob = mu_m)
    
  } else if (mediator$dist == "continuous") {
    bootdata$m_dox_ref  <-  mu_m_dox_ref
    bootdata$m_dox_idx  <-  mu_m_dox_idx
    
    bootdata$dom_int    <- rnorm(n, mean = mu_m, sd = sd_m)
    
  } else {
    stop("mediator$dist must be either binary or continuous")
  }
  
  var_names2 <- bootdata %>% select(-c({{time_var}})) %>% colnames()
  
  bootdata_long_new <- bootdata %>% #updating the new long data with the mediator information
    tidyr::expand(nesting(!!!syms(var_names2)), time=as.double(0:(max(event_date_mos)-1))) %>% 
    mutate(censored = case_when((time>=event_date_mos & !!sym(outcome$name)==0)~1, 
                                TRUE~0),
           current_event = case_when((time>=event_date_mos-1 & !!sym(outcome$name)==1)~1, 
                                     TRUE~0)) %>% 
    group_by(id) %>% 
    mutate(past_event = lag(current_event),
           past_event = case_when(is.na(past_event)~0,
                                  TRUE~past_event))
  
  #Y stage
  
  #PDE
  bootdata_long_new$surv_y_x1_m_x0_pde <- 1 - predict.glm(model_y,
                                                          newdata = bootdata_long_new %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=1, !!sym(mediator$name):=m_dox_ref), 
                                                          type = "response")
  
  
  bootdata_long_new$surv_y_x0_m_x0_pde <- 1 - predict.glm(model_y,
                                                          newdata = bootdata_long_new %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=0, !!sym(mediator$name):=m_dox_ref), 
                                                          type = "response")
  
  
  #TIE
  bootdata_long_new$surv_y_x1_m_x1_tie <- 1 - predict.glm(model_y,
                                                          newdata = bootdata_long_new %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=1, !!sym(mediator$name):=m_dox_idx), 
                                                          type = "response")
  
  
  bootdata_long_new$surv_y_x1_m_x0_tie <- 1 - predict.glm(model_y,
                                                          newdata = bootdata_long_new %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=1, !!sym(mediator$name):=m_dox_ref), 
                                                          type = "response")
  
  
  #TE
  bootdata_long_new$surv_y_x1_m_x1_te <- 1 - predict.glm(model_y,
                                                         newdata = bootdata_long_new %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=1, !!sym(mediator$name):=m_dox_idx), 
                                                         type = "response")
  
  bootdata_long_new$surv_y_x0_m_x0_te <- 1 - predict.glm(model_y,
                                                         newdata = bootdata_long_new %>% mutate(!!sym(exposure$name):=0, !!sym(mediator$name):=m_dox_ref), 
                                                         type = "response")
  
  
  te <- survival_estimates(data=bootdata_long_new, id="id", treated="surv_y_x1_m_x1_te",untreated="surv_y_x0_m_x0_te")
  
  pde <- survival_estimates(data=bootdata_long_new, id="id",treated="surv_y_x1_m_x0_pde",untreated="surv_y_x0_m_x0_pde")
  tie <- survival_estimates(data=bootdata_long_new, id="id",treated="surv_y_x1_m_x1_tie",untreated="surv_y_x1_m_x0_tie")

  
  if(length(mediator$covariates) == 0){
    medcov = "None"
  } else {
    medcov = glue_collapse(mediator$covariates, sep=" + ")
  }
  
  
  if(length(outcome$covariates) == 0){
    outcov = "None"
  } else {
    outcov = glue_collapse(outcome$covariates, sep=" + ")
  }
  
  final_res <- 
    tibble(
      variables = glue("exposure = ", exposure$name, 
                       ", mediator = ", mediator$name, 
                       ", outcome = ", outcome$name,
                       "medcov = ", medcov,
                       "outcov = ", outcov),
      bind_rows(
        te$results, pde$results, tie$results
      ))
  

    return(final_res) 
  
  
}

gform_mediation_survival_all <- function(list_interv0=list_interv_mediators){
  res <- pmap_dfr(list_interv0, 
                  gform_mediation_survival, 
                  data=salsa_analytical,
                  time_var = "time_to_dementia_cind_yrs",
                  old_time_scale= "years",
                  new_time_scale= "months")
  return(res)
}

                                          .progress = TRUE)

df <- results_bootsamples_surv_mediation %>% 
  list_transpose() %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% 
  unnest(col=result) 

p_load("forstringr", "formattable")

set.seed(123)
df1 <- df %>% 
  mutate(mediator = str_extract_part(str_extract_part(variables, before=T, pattern=", outcome = "), 
                                     before=F, pattern=", mediator = ")) %>% 
  select(-c(variables)) %>% 
  relocate(mediator) %>% 
  filter(warnings=="character(0)") %>% 
  group_by(mediator, estimate) %>% 
  dplyr::slice_sample(n=200) %>% #to select a random sample of 200 bootstrap among converging models
  mutate(replication=1:n()) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  relocate(replication, mediator) %>% 
  select(replication, mediator, estimate, RR_ave, RD_ave)



results_final_surv_mediation <- df1 %>% 
  mutate_at(c("RR_ave"), log) %>% 
  select(mediator, estimate, RR_ave, RD_ave) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols=-c(estimate, mediator),
               names_to = c("effect_type"),
               values_to = "value") %>% 
  group_by(estimate, effect_type, mediator) %>% 
  group_modify(~ {.x %>% map_dfr(simulr::pestimate_tbl)}) %>% 
  mutate(estimate=case_when(estimate=="0_pde"~"pde",
                            estimate=="1_tie"~"tie",
                            estimate=="1_te"~"te",
                            TRUE~estimate)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% 
  mutate(Mean = case_when(effect_type=="RR_ave"~exp(Mean),
                          TRUE~Mean),
         `p2.5th` = case_when(effect_type=="RR_ave"~exp(`p2.5th`),
                          TRUE~`p2.5th`),
         `p97.5th` = case_when(effect_type=="RR_ave"~exp(`p97.5th`),
                          TRUE~`p97.5th`)) %>% 
  select(mediator, estimate, effect_type, Mean, `p2.5th`, `p97.5th`) %>% 
  arrange(mediator, estimate, effect_type) %>% 
  filter(effect_type=="RR_ave") %>% 
  select(-effect_type) %>% 
  pivot_wider(values_from = -c("estimate", "mediator"),
              names_from = "estimate",
              names_glue = "{.value}_{estimate}") %>% 
  rename_all(str_to_lower) %>% 
  set_colnames(str_replace_all(colnames(.), "[.]", "_")) %>%
  mutate(prop_mediated = log(mean_tie)/log(mean_te),
         pde_ci = simulr::ci_fct(pe=mean_pde, 
                                 low= p2_5th_pde, 
                                 high = p97_5th_pde,
                        scale=""),
         tie_ci = simulr::ci_fct(pe=mean_tie, 
                                 low= p2_5th_tie, 
                                 high = p97_5th_tie,
                                 scale=""),
         prop_mediated = round(prop_mediated*100,0)) %>% 
  select(mediator, pde_ci, tie_ci, prop_mediated) %>% 
  mutate(mediator = case_when(mediator=="fv0_hscrp_cont"~"1-High-sensitivity C-Reactive Protein (CRP)",
                              mediator=="fv0_il_6_cont"~"2-Interleukin 6 (IL-6)",
                              mediator=="fv0_tnf_a_cont"~"3-Tumor Necrosis Factor alpha (TNF-𝜶)",
                              mediator=="fv0_current_smoking"~"4-Current smoking",
                              mediator=="fv0_alcohol_day_week"~"5-Daily or weekly alcohol consumption",
                              mediator=="fv0_deptot_score"~"6-Depressive symptom score")) %>% 
  arrange(mediator)

salsa0 <- salsa %>% 
  transmute(
    nativity_3cat,
    born_in_us = simulr::d(nativity_3cat %in% c(2)),
    mexican_orient_scale = rowMeans(across(all_of(mexican_orient_scale_vars)), na.rm = T),
    anglo_orient_scale = rowMeans(across(all_of(anglo_orient_scale_vars)), na.rm = T),
    accult_diff_score = anglo_orient_scale - mexican_orient_scale,
    accult_3cat = case_when(accult_diff_score>0 ~ "high",
                            accult_diff_score<0 ~ "low",
                            TRUE ~ "bicultural"),
    high_accult = factor(simulr::d(accult_3cat %in% c("high","bicultural")))
  ) %>% set_variable_labels(high_accult = "Acculturation level (score >=0)",
                            accult_diff_score = simulr::str_wrapr(string="Acculturation score = Anglo orientation scale - Mexican oriention scale",
                                                          width = 80))
